# Agile Process Notes for QA Project

## Sprint Planning
- 1-week sprint cycle for testing new features
- Each test cycle aligned with story acceptance criteria

## QA Activities per Sprint
- Test Planning: Define scope for the sprint
- Test Execution: Run test cases and exploratory testing
- Bug Reporting: Report defects with severity, priority, and business impact
- Regression Testing: Verify fixes from previous sprint
- Test Summary: Deliver report at sprint end

## Integration with Agile Workflow
- Bugs tracked in GitHub Issues (or Jira)
- User stories mapped to test cases via Traceability Matrix
- Sprint reviews provide QA feedback to Product Owner and Dev team

## Business Perspective
- Focus on revenue-impacting areas (checkout, authentication)
- Usability issues flagged for UX improvement
- High-risk defects prioritized to reduce operational impact
